am\": \"this year's games\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympicsdue\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 461}, {\"ngram\": \"a case\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 471}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"twisties\", \"from\": 475, \"to\": 488}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite its amusing name, the twisties refers to a psychological condition similar to the \\\"yips\\\", or even writer's block, where a person who usually is proficient in a particular skill (in this case gymnastics) is suddenly unable to perform under pressure.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 748, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its amusing name\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 516}, {\"ngram\": \"the twisties\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"a psychological condition\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 566}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"yips\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"even writer's block\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 628}, {\"ngram\": \"a particular skill\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 676}, {\"ngram\": \"this case\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 690}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 691, \"to\": 701}, {\"ngram\": \"pressure\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles hasdescribed the conditionas like being \\\"lost in the air\\\", saying \\\"your mind and your body are at a disconnect.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 867, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"the conditionas\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 784}, {\"ngram\": \"the air\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 812}, {\"ngram\": \"your mind\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"your body\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"a disconnect\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 866}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Your body is going to try to do something, and your mind is going to be like, 'No, you are not doing this'\\\".\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Your body\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 877}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 909}, {\"ngram\": \"your mind\", \"from\": 915, \"to\": 924}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite not possessing nearly the same level of skill as Biles, I have experienced my own version of the twisties many times - as, I imagine, have many people.\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nearly the same level\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"skill\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1031}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"my own version\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"the twisties\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1091}, {\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1136}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is nothing worse than suddenly experiencing that sensation of vertigo when doing something you have done many times before.\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1154}, {\"ngram\": \"that sensation\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"vertigo\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1213}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"many times\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1259}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Luckily, must of us do not experience iton the world stage.\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1327, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1287}, {\"ngram\": \"the world stage\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Returning to this year's Olympics after such an episode is an inspiration, and a reminder that no matter how hard we fall, we can always pick ourselves back up again.\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this year's Olympics\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1362}, {\"ngram\": \"such an episode\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1384}, {\"ngram\": \"an inspiration\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1402}, {\"ngram\": \"a reminder\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1418}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephen Bloom Canterbury I was interested to read in Sunday's edition that Dame Priti Patel wouldhand back some control of policy to ordinary party membersand allow them to elect key officials.\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1692, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sunday's edition\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"wouldhand\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"some control\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1616}, {\"ngram\": \"policy\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"ordinary party membersand\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1655}, {\"ngram\": \"key officials\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1689}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those are presumably the same ordinary party members who elected Liz Truss as leader and prime minister.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1759, \"end\": 1768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liz_Truss\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Liz Truss\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liz_Truss\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liz_Truss\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same ordinary party members\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1746}, {\"ngram\": \"leader\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"prime minister\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1797}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What can possibly go wrong?\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"John Coppendale Cambridge The new government is to be commended for its publicly stated objective to govern with openness and transparency.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9798886821692542, \"rank\": 0.020523997072719114, \"text\": \"Cambridge\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The new government\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"its publicly stated objective\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"openness\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1949}, {\"ngram\": \"transparency\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 1966}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is desperately needed following years of Tory deceits, obfuscation and corruption.\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"obfuscation\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2041}, {\"ngram\": \"corruption\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2056}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is crucial to restore trust in democracy and UK politics.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2106, \"end\": 2117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Politics_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK politics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Politics_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Politics_of_the_United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"trust\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2088}, {\"ngram\": \"democracy\", \"from\": 2092, \"to\": 2101}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone - the public, our institutions, business, the media, the trade unions, so-called \\\"think tanks\\\" and pressure groups - all have their own vested interests in promoting their own version of honesty.\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2141}, {\"ngram\": \"our institutions\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2159}, {\"ngram\": \"business\", \"from\": 2161, \"to\": 2169}, {\"ngram\": \"the media\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2180}, {\"ngram\": \"the trade unions\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2198}, {\"ngram\": \"so-called \\\"think tanks\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2222}, {\"ngram\": \"pressure groups\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2243}, {\"ngram\": \"their own vested interests\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2281}, {\"ngram\": \"their own version\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2312}, {\"ngram\": \"honesty\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of us have an incomplete picture of, for example, the state of the economy, and few are in a position to give a balanced view.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2335}, {\"ngram\": \"an incomplete picture\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2362}, {\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2378}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2389}, {\"ngram\": \"the economy\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2404}, {\"ngram\": \"a position\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2431}, {\"ngram\": \"a balanced view\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2455}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that will not prevent many from expressing their own version of events.\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2532, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their own version\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2521}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2531}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will get personal, aggressive and feed the populist vultures.\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2599, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the populist vultures\", \"from\": 2577, \"to\": 2598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be easy to ascribe ulterior motives to our new, open and transparent government.\", \"from\": 2601, \"to\": 2689, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ulterior motives\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2644}, {\"ngram\": \"our new, open and transparent government\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We need to focus on the facts, and we need to cut the new government some slack.\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2771, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the facts\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"the new government\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2759}, {\"ngram\": \"some slack\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Openness and transparency are so much more difficult than the half-truths, partial pictures and ideological bias that we have become accustomed to, and take a heavy toll on the personal honesty and integrity of its champions.\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2997, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Openness\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2780}, {\"ngram\": \"transparency\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2797}, {\"ngram\": \"the half-truths\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 2845}, {\"ngram\": \"partial pictures\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2863}, {\"ngram\": \"ideological bias\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2884}, {\"ngram\": \"a heavy toll\", \"from\": 2929, \"to\": 2941}, {\"ngram\": \"the personal honesty\", \"from\": 2945, \"to\": 2965}, {\"ngram\": \"integrity\", \"from\": 2970, \"to\": 2979}, {\"ngram\": \"its champions\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 2996}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a risky management style, but it is the right one.\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3054, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a risky management style\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Is the country ready for it, or will bitterness and cynicism continue to prevail?\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3137, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3070}, {\"ngram\": \"bitterness\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3103}, {\"ngram\": \"cynicism\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"David Lowndes Southampton I, along with I am sure many people, am having trouble adjusting to a media cycle which does not confront us with some cringeworthy government embarrassment or outrage every 48 hours.\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3350, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"David\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3144}, {\"ngram\": \"Southampton I\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3166}, {\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 3189, \"to\": 3200}, {\"ngram\": \"trouble\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3219}, {\"ngram\": \"a media cycle\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3246}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3271, \"to\": 3273}, {\"ngram\": \"some cringeworthy government embarrassment\", \"from\": 3279, \"to\": 3321}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Labour are by no means perfect, but it cannot be denied that they are much better at keeping their heads down and getting on with the job - so far, at least.\", \"from\": 3352, \"to\": 3509, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Labour\", \"from\": 3352, \"to\": 3358}, {\"ngram\": \"no means\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3374}, {\"ngram\": \"their heads\", \"from\": 3445, \"to\": 3456}, {\"ngram\": \"the job\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3489}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us just hope that it lasts.\", \"from\": 3511, \"to\": 3542, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3515, \"to\": 3517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Molly Howe Liverpool Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3544, \"to\": 3797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3544, \"end\": 3549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"score\": 0.9999628759721314, \"rank\": 2.870551650301835e-05, \"text\": \"Molly\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\"}, {\"begin\": 3556, \"end\": 3565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.8271059889845337, \"rank\": 0.2090325991461282, \"text\": \"Liverpool\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 